## The Core Revelation: AMH Does Not Predict Natural Conception

Many women mistakenly believe their AMH (Anti-Müllerian Hormone) level directly predicts their ability to conceive naturally. However, **extensive research involving over 28,000 individuals reveals AMH levels are not a significant predictor of natural conception**. This finding challenges a common misconception.

A large meta-analysis highlighted that among women not identified as infertile and actively trying to conceive, AMH levels did not correlate with reduced fertility (Steiner et al., 2017). This emphasizes that AMH alone should not be the sole determinant of fertility expectations.

